### Output Files (per model)

```
surface_reconstruction/iteration_3000/
├── fused_mesh.ply                # Step 1: tissue surface from TSDF fusion
├── fused_pointcloud.ply          # Step 1: colored point cloud
├── camera_trajectory.json        # Step 1: original camera poses
├── synthetic_organ.ply           # Step 2: simulated CT organ model
├── organ_metadata.json           # Step 2: organ geometry metadata
├── registered_endo_mesh.ply      # Step 2: endo mesh aligned to organ
├── registered_trajectory.json    # Step 2: camera path in organ coords
├── registration_transform.json   # Step 2: ICP transform matrix
└── navigation_scene.ply          # Step 2: combined scene for viewing
```

## How to Run

```bash
# Full pipeline for a model:
python extract_surface.py --model_path output/endonerf/pulling --configs arguments/endonerf.py
python create_synthetic_organ.py --model_path output/endonerf/pulling
python register_to_organ.py --model_path output/endonerf/pulling
python visualize_navigation.py --model_path output/endonerf/pulling
```

## Key Fix

Fixed camera trajectory extraction in [extract_surface.py](file:///home/mi3dr/Endo-4DGS/extract_surface.py) — now uses `view.world_view_transform` and `view.camera_center` directly from the Camera class instead of re-deriving from R/T (which had a transpose bug giving all-zero positions).

## Visualization

The [visualize_navigation.py](file:///home/mi3dr/Endo-4DGS/visualize_navigation.py) script opens an interactive 3D viewer showing:
- **Organ model** (pink ellipsoid)
- **Endoscopic mesh** registered inside the organ
- **Camera path** colored green→red (time progression)
- **Camera frustums** showing viewing direction at intervals
- **Start** (green) and **End** (red) markers

> [!NOTE]
> On headless servers, the viewer may not display. Use the exported `navigation_scene.ply` in MeshLab or any 3D viewer.
